# Veil agent — documentation actualization

Documentation is part of the **agent chain**, not an optional cleanup. After code merges, the orchestrator (or implementer before handoff) updates the artifacts the next agent will read.

## Where agents read truth

| Artifact | When to update |
|----------|----------------|
| **Master / phase plans** (`.cursor/plans/`) | Phase `done`, merge SHA, branch cleared |
| **[README.md](../../README.md)** | Architecture status table, quick start, test matrix, deploy overview |
| **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** | New `make test-*` targets, workflow steps, layer rules |
| **[CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md)** | Contributor test matrix, doc expectations |
| **[.github/repo-description.txt](../../.github/repo-description.txt)** | One-line GitHub summary (~350 chars); then `make sync-github-metadata` |
| **Runtime docs** (`docs/threatintel-runtime.md`, `docs/engage-runtime.md`) | Ports, env vars, compose overlays, smokes |
| **Contracts** (`docs/ingest-contract.md`, `docs/schemas/`) | `pkg/harvest`, `pkg/commit` wire changes |
| **Platform / deploy** ([docs/platform-closed-loop-pilot.md](../../docs/platform-closed-loop-pilot.md), [docs/deploy-platform-hybrid.md](../../docs/deploy-platform-hybrid.md)) | Bus, loop smokes, TF/Ansible/Helm |
| **Parity / audit** (`docs/engage-*.md`, CSV matrices) | Routes, catalog, MCP triangle changes |

Do **not** edit `.external/` or duplicate HexStrike prose; link to Veil docs instead.

## Agent chain (end-to-end)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  plan[Master + phase plan]
  impl[Implementer on branch]
  test[Layer + phase tests]
  pr[PR / push branch]
  critic[Critic review]
  merge[Merge + push main]
  docs[Documentation actualization]
  next[Next phase from main]
  plan --> impl --> test --> pr --> critic
  critic -->|APPROVE| merge --> docs --> next
  critic -->|REQUEST_CHANGES| impl
```

1. **Plan** — scope, DoD, dependencies, status table (`phase / branch / owner`).
2. **Implement** — one phase per branch ([veil-agent-parallel-branches.mdc](veil-agent-parallel-branches.mdc)).
3. **Verify** — commands from phase plan + [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) checklist.
4. **Critic** — [veil-agent-critic.mdc](veil-agent-critic.mdc); APPROVE only when DoD is evidenced.
5. **Merge** — prompt merge to `main`; no stacked unmerged phases.
6. **Document** — this rule: plans, runtime, AGENTS, CONTRIBUTING as applicable.
7. **Next** — new branch from `git pull origin main`.

## Documentation checklist (after merge)

Copy into PR comment or phase closeout:

```markdown
### Docs actualization
- [ ] Master plan: phase N → done, merge SHA
- [ ] Phase plan: status completed
- [ ] README.md — status table, tests, deploy section if user-facing change
- [ ] CONTRIBUTING.md — test matrix / workflow if contributor steps changed
- [ ] .github/repo-description.txt + `make sync-github-metadata` if one-line summary changed
- [ ] Runtime / env docs if compose or API changed
- [ ] AGENTS.md if new tests or agent workflow steps
- [ ] Schemas / ingest-contract if pkg wire types changed
- [ ] Engage parity CSV/matrix if routes or catalog changed
- [ ] deploy/README + hybrid doc if deploy paths changed
```

## Reasoning quality (plans and reviews)

When writing or reviewing **phase plans** and critic notes, prefer explicit structure over vague goals:

| Technique | Use in Veil agents |
|-----------|-------------------|
| **Chain-of-thought (private)** | Break DoD into verify steps before claiming done |
| **Few-shot** | In phase plans, link one **good** prior phase (e.g. Platform P0–P3 table) as pattern for scope/DoD |
| **Constraint-first** | State architecture bans first (no cross-import, NATS-only integration) |
| **Counterfactual check** | «What would fail in CI?» — list the exact `make` / smoke commands |
| **5 Whys / Kaizen** | On failures: [veil-agent-kaizen-metacognition.mdc](veil-agent-kaizen-metacognition.mdc) before the next fix |

Phase plan template (minimal):

```markdown
## Scope
## Out of scope
## Files
## Acceptance (commands)
## Docs to touch on merge
```

